source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-kale-tomato-feta-panini-6411e8515ce27546ad08049f
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Swap in asparagus for potatoes; roast until tender and lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes}. (Save potatoes for another use.)

While potatoes roast, peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Quarter @lemon{1}. Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds and season with salt and pepper. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}; chop into bite-size pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), and a pinch of garlic. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add kale and remaining garlic; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer kale to a second small bowl; stir in @cream cheese{2%tbsp} until combined. Wipe out pan.

Spread half the @sourdough bread{4%slices} slices with creamy kale; top with even layers of @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, and tomato.

Spread remaining sourdough slices with Dijonnaise (save some for serving).

Close sandwiches.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for kale over medium heat. Once hot, add sandwiches and push around in pan until melted butter has absorbed. (For 4 servings, work in batches or use a second pan, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.) Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is slightly melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add another @butter{1%tbsp} to pan, then flip sandwiches and push around again until melted butter has absorbed. Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese is fully melted, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If you have a heavy-bottomed pan, place on top of the sandwiches as they cook for a real panini experience!

Squeeze one lemon wedge over potatoes (two wedges for 4 servings).

Halve panini on a diagonal and divide between plates. Serve with potato wedges and remaining Dijonnaise on the side for dipping.

> Squeeze one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings) over asparagus.